the night time life in the dark wood of Nektulous. The cresent moon was barely visible over the mountains, silvering the fog but shedding no light as it neared setting. Silent as the mist, eyes as gold as the setting cresent, a pale wolf padded the silent trees far from the dark elves' home.<br>
The she-wolf paused and scented the still air. This was not the first time she wandered the lonely reaches of Nektulous in search of answers within herself. She fought with her teachings, debated with long-past mentors, argued with the morals bred into her. This night was no different as she padded along the shadowed game-trail, her passing as silent as a ghost.  When she was younger, she would have run and lived and hunted with the wolf packs of Faydark until the solution made itself clear, but those days were past. Now she had a pack of her own, and one that would tear her apart if she moved the wrong way.<br>
One paw after another, down the darkened path. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bonds of loyalty, bonds of love, bonds of blood. These the elven races shared, even in the darkness of Neriak.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> A slight wind blows through the thick trees, stirring the fog. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hatred spread across the world, but thin as water. Except among the Chosen.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> A scent fills her nostrils, that of a traveler in the woods.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hatred as a feeling, as only mere words in the masses of Norrath.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The wolf began to lope towards the scent, silent as the moon. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Carelessly flung in rages and unwittingly, full of meaningless fury.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The high elf was in sight, resting uneasily in the woods of the dark elves.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hatred was crimson blood, thick as the night in cavern depths.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The she-wolf leapt at the pale figure, teeth bared in a silent snarl. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> It was powerful and dark, the Father's own hands.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Jaws clamped about the woman's throat, her struggles ignored by the white beast. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> A force of its own in the hands of the weilder.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The elf fell back, balance lost by the heavy wolf at her neck. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> A blade to be weilded at any cost.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The lupine spread her paws and twisted, tearing out the elf's throat with a sound of ripping cartilage. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> A fire to be kept alive at any cost.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
The rich taste thrilled through her, bringing her back to herself. Her inner turmoil had ceased in the unexpected rush of hatred. Red stained her pure white pelt, muzzle almost black with the hot blood. The hatred had flowed into her with a driving fury that drowned out all arguments. She shivered not from the chill of the hour, but with a savage joy of the power rushing through her after the kill. Never before had she been so close to the deity she had turned to, and now she bowed to His touch with eagerness. <br>
When she left the tiny clearing, she walked on silent elven feet.  Her skin was covered with the life blood of the slain high elf, the holy symbol of Tunare taken from the victim's breast clutched in her hand.  The halflings in the woods would find the high elf come morning, and when they did... Lyri smiled to the dark sky. <p><P ALIGN=CENTER>Lyri Corinthar<BR>
